Title: Scattering of closed strings from many D-branes
Authors: M. Frau, I. Pesando, S. Sciuto, A. Lerda, R. Russo
Comments: 15 pages, plain Latex
Report-no: DFTT 8/97
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B400 (1997) 52-62
\\
  We develop an operator formalism to compute scattering amplitudes of
arbitrary bosonic string states in the background of many D-branes.
Specifically, we construct a suitable boundary state which we use to saturate
the multi-Reggeon vertex in order to obtain the generator of multi-membrane
scattering amplitudes. We explicitly show that the amplitudes with $h$ parallel
D-branes are similar to amplitudes with $h-1$ open string loops.
